webpackJsonp([0x7530a554e7a5],{1197:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Justin Ball",author:"Justin Ball"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/jbasdf/projects/justinball/src/posts/2012-12-05-hack-the-lglv5500-into-a-pvr/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>I\'ve had this TV for a while. Turns out that accessing the services menu isn\'t to terribly hard if you have a programmable remote. (In my case a Logitech Harmony). The TV supports DVR functionality if you add a USB Hard drive and turn it on in the service menu.</p>\n<p><strong>Warning: you can brick your TV and make it unusable. Be careful!!</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Step one is to setup your remote. Details:\n<a href="http://openlgtv.org.ru/wiki/index.php/Access_service_menus_with_universal_remote">http://openlgtv.org.ru/wiki/index.php/Access<em>service</em>menus<em>with</em>universal_remote</a></li>\n<li>This post talks about the options:\n<a href="http://www.avsforum.com/t/1322953/2011-lg-xxlv5500-smarttv-impressions/210">http://www.avsforum.com/t/1322953/2011-lg-xxlv5500-smarttv-impressions/210</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Update:\nThere\'s a python script you can use to access your TV from your PC:\n<a href="https://github.com/ubaransel/lgcommander">https://github.com/ubaransel/lgcommander</a></p>\n<p>There\'s also a little more information here on the menus:\n<a href="http://openlgtv.org.ru/wiki/index.php/Hidden_service_modes_/_menus">http://openlgtv.org.ru/wiki/index.php/Hidden<em>service</em>modes<em>/</em>menus</a></p>\n<p>That\'s pretty much it. Once the usb drive is recognized the pause button on your remote should start working.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"Hack the LGLV5500 into a PVR",date:"December 05, 2012",imageUrl:null,structuredHtml:null,image:null}}},pathContext:{path:"/hack-the-lglv5500-into-a-pvr"}}}});
